						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1524 (1603 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the gift of his share of the temple offerings which he had obtained with libation of water from the Nāyakas of the lineage of Kṛishṇappa-nāyaka, by Kēśavaiyaṅgār for running a <hi rend="italic">Rāmānujakūṭam</hi> to feed ten Śrīvaishṇavas every day. <hi rend="bold">The Śaka year 15[2]4 corresponds to Śubhakṛit not Śōbhakṛit. For Śubhakṛit the details Mīṉa, ba. 11, Sunday, Sravishṭhā correspond regularly to 1603, A.D. March 27, f.d.t. ·21; ·84.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
